# --------------------------
# Basic Terminal Commands Cheat Sheet
# --------------------------

# 1) File Operations
Create a file:            nano <filename>
Read a file:              cat <filename>
Edit a file:              nano <filename>
List all files:           ls
List files with details:  ls -lah
Copy a file:              cp <source> <destination>
Move/Rename a file:       mv <source> <destination>
Delete a file:            rm <filename>

# 2) Directory Operations
Change directory:         cd <directory>
Go to home directory:     cd ~
Go back one level:        cd ..
Make a new directory:     mkdir <directory>
Remove a directory:       rmdir <directory>   # only if empty
Remove directory and content: rm -r <directory>
Show current directory:   pwd

# 3) Permissions & Admin
Run admin command:        sudo <command>
Switch user:              su - <username>
Show current user:        whoami
Change file permissions:  chmod <mode> <file>
Change file owner:        chown <user>:<group> <file>

# 4) Compressed Files
Unzip a file:             unzip <file.zip>
Read zip content:         unzip -p <file.zip> | less
Create a zip file:        zip <archive.zip> <files>
Extract tar.gz:           tar -xvzf <file.tar.gz>
Create tar.gz:            tar -czvf <archive.tar.gz> <files>

# 5) Networking
Check IP address:         ip addr show
Ping a host:              ping <host>
Check open ports:         netstat -tuln
Download a file:          curl -O <url>
SSH to another machine:   ssh <username>@<ip_address>

# 6) System Info
Disk usage:               df -h
Memory usage:             free -h
List processes:           ps aux
Real-time process monitor: htop
Check uptime:             uptime
Check system version:     uname -a

# 7) Git / Version Control
Check git status:         git status
Add changes:              git add <file>
Commit changes:           git commit -m "<commit message>"
Push to remote:           git push
Pull from remote:         git pull
Show commit log:          git log

# 8) Exiting / Navigation
Exit a program/view:      q   # e.g., less, man
Cancel a command:         Ctrl+C
Clear terminal:           clear
